Avian humanoids of the western sky-roads, the Serathi predate the Keeper surveyors by
generations and navigate by sky-lines — the horizon profiles of ridges and canopies
that form a map legible only from altitude. They maintain roost-chronicles of continuous
aerial observation older than most human cities, and the Roc Road was built along a
corridor the Serathi had been flying for centuries before it was named. Their
relationship with every ground-bound civilization follows the same pattern: their courier
services and aerial intelligence are valued, their territorial claims over the sky-roads
they have used since before memory are perpetually deferred. The negotiations continue.
The sky-readers do not appear to be in a hurry.
